answers.q: aia e203 is a contract document that has which of the following information:
answers.a: In food labeling, E203 refers to calcium sorbate, a synthetic preservative (the calcium salt of sorbic acid) that inhibits molds and yeasts; it is unrelated to AIA contract documents.
